1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3563 By: Eaves
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to commercial motor vehicles;
prohibiting the operation of commercial motor
8 vehicles by unauthorized migrants; requiring law
enforcement officers to take unauthorized migrants
9 operating commercial motor vehicles into custody and
facilitate the transfer to a federal immigration
10 agency; implementing punitive fees and required
costs; prohibiting certain persons from operating
11 business in the state; providing for codification;
providing an effective date; and declaring an
12 emergency.
13
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-126.3 of Title 47, unless
19 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. A law enforcement officer who determines that a person
21 operating a commercial motor vehicle in this state is an
22 unauthorized migrant shall take the unauthorized migrant into
23 custody and facilitate the transfer of the unauthorized migrant into
24
Req. No. 13964 Page 1

1 the custody of a federal immigration agency consistent with federal
2 law.
3 B. A commercial motor vehicle operated by an unauthorized
4 migrant who is taken into custody pursuant to this section shall be
5 impounded. The owner of the compounded vehicle shall pay a Fifty
6 Thousand Dollar ($50,000.00) fine to the Department of Public Safety
7 and all costs and fees for the impoundment, including the cost of
8 notification, before the impounded vehicle may be released to such
9 owner.
10 C. A motor carrier that owns, leases, or otherwise operates a
11 commercial motor vehicle operated by a person who is taken into
12 custody pursuant to this section shall be prohibited from operating
13 in this state.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
15 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
16 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
17 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
18 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
